crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Linux Remote Access Trojan (RAT) or backdoor disguised as a JDK/Gradle update utility. It contains a full set of command-and-control (C2) features including arbitrary remote command execution (RCE) via popen, file upload (exfiltration), and file download (infiltration). The malware communicates with the hardcoded C2 domain 'jdkgradle.com' using HTTP/HTTPS POST requests via libcurl. It implements a custom protocol for handling tasks like 'MsgCmd' (execute and return output), 'MsgRun' (execute in background), and 'MsgDown' (download file to disk). Notable IOCs include the domain 'jdkgradle.com', the URI path '/jdk/update/check', and the local log file '/tmp/xweb_log.md'.
